<title>USA: SEC investigates Donnkenny  - WSJ.</title>
<headline>SEC investigates Donnkenny  - WSJ.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-12-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Apparel maker Donnkenny Inc said the Securities and Exchange Commission is conducting a formal investigation into its financial statements and trading in its securities, The Wall Street Journal reported Monday.</p>
<p>News of the investigation follows a tumultuous downturn culminating with last week's resignation of chief executive officer Richard Rubin, whose departure came after the company announced last fall that it would have to restate six fiscal quarters of results due to improperly recorded sales and expenses, the story says.</p>
